## Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this React + Vite project.

### What Was Implemented

**1. Fetched Latest Documentation**
- Retrieved the most up-to-date installation instructions from the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart)
- Identified that this project uses React with Vite, requiring the React-specific integration

**2. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package version ^1.0.15 using npm
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json with the new dependency

**3. Component Integration**
- Modified `src/App.jsx` to import the SpeedInsights component from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Added the `<SpeedInsights />` component alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component at the root level of the application
- Followed the same integration pattern as the existing Vercel Analytics implementation

### Files Modified

**client/package.json**
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` to dependencies

**client/package-lock.json**
- Updated with new dependency tree for Speed Insights package

**client/src/App.jsx**
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
- Added component: `<SpeedInsights />` in the return statement, placed after `<Analytics />`

### Implementation Decisions

1. **Placement**: The SpeedInsights component was added at the root level of the App component, right after the existing Analytics component. This ensures it loads on every page and tracks performance metrics across the entire application.

2. **Framework-Specific Package**: Used `@vercel/speed-insights/react` as specified in the Vercel documentation for React applications, ensuring optimal integration with the React lifecycle.

3. **Consistency**: Followed the same pattern as the existing Vercel Analytics integration already present in the project.

### Verification Completed

✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✅ No new linting errors introduced
✅ Project compiles without errors
✅ Lock file updated with new dependencies

### Next Steps

To see Speed Insights data in the Vercel dashboard:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. After users visit the site, performance metrics will appear in the Speed Insights tab within a few days

### Notes

- The project already had Vercel Analytics installed, so Speed Insights was added alongside it
- Pre-existing linting warnings/errors in the project were not addressed as they are unrelated to this implementation
- No tests were available to run (no test script configured in package.json)
